: \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Phenotype\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Phenotype\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the introduction\", \"from\": 399, \"to\": 415}, {\"ngram\": \"the return\", \"from\": 441, \"to\": 451}, {\"ngram\": \"the Olympics\", \"from\": 455, \"to\": 467}, {\"ngram\": \"time\", \"from\": 474, \"to\": 478}, {\"ngram\": \"another predictable global uproar\", \"from\": 483, \"to\": 516}, {\"ngram\": \"the female category\", \"from\": 548, \"to\": 567}]}, {\"sentence\": \"This is now a century-old problem in elite sport that we have somehow not yet managed to solve in a uniform way.\", \"from\": 570, \"to\": 682, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"a century-old problem\", \"from\": 582, \"to\": 603}, {\"ngram\": \"elite sport\", \"from\": 607, \"to\": 618}, {\"ngram\": \"a uniform way\", \"from\": 668, \"to\": 681}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The Paris 2024 iteration of this debate is arguably the most explosive ever due to a confluence of at least three factors: \\u2026 I will close by reiterating the three basic points that I and other experts in girls' and women's sport have been making for a long time.\", \"from\": 683, \"to\": 947, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 687, \"end\": 697, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2024_Summer_Olympics\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.9794665944427258e-15, \"text\": \"Paris 2024\", \"types\": [\"Q1656682\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2024_Summer_Olympics\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2024_Summer_Olympics\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"this debate\", \"from\": 711, \"to\": 722}, {\"ngram\": \"a confluence\", \"from\": 766, \"to\": 778}, {\"ngram\": \"at least three factors\", \"from\": 782, \"to\": 804}, {\"ngram\": \"the three basic points\", \"from\": 836, \"to\": 858}, {\"ngram\": \"other experts\", \"from\": 870, \"to\": 883}, {\"ngram\": \"girls' and women's sport\", \"from\": 887, \"to\": 911}, {\"ngram\": \"a long time\", \"from\": 933, \"to\": 944}]}, {\"sentence\": \"First, the female category in elite sport has noraison d'\\u00eatreapart from the biological sex differences that lead to sex differences in performance and the gap between the top male and female athletes.\", \"from\": 949, \"to\": 1149, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the female category\", \"from\": 956, \"to\": 975}, {\"ngram\": \"elite sport\", \"from\": 979, \"to\": 990}, {\"ngram\": \"noraison d'\\u00eatreapart\", \"from\": 995, \"to\": 1015}, {\"ngram\": \"the biological sex differences\", \"from\": 1021, \"to\": 1051}, {\"ngram\": \"sex differences\", \"from\": 1065, \"to\": 1080}, {\"ngram\": \"performance\", \"from\": 1084, \"to\": 1095}, {\"ngram\": \"the gap\", \"from\": 1100, \"to\": 1107}, {\"ngram\": \"the top male and female athletes\", \"from\": 1116, \"to\": 1148}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The suggestion that we could choose to rationalise the category differently-for instance, on the basis of self-declared gender identity-or that we could make increasingly numerous exceptions in the interests of inclusion (as the IOC seems to have done to allow Khelif and Lin to compete in Paris) has no legs outside of certain progressive enclaves.\", \"from\": 1150, \"to\": 1499, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1379, \"end\": 1382, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 7.998446553957215e-16, \"text\": \"IOC\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\"}, {\"begin\": 1440, \"end\": 1445, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 0.9997496974353504, \"rank\": 0.00025036523177225336, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"The suggestion\", \"from\": 1150, \"to\": 1164}, {\"ngram\": \"the category\", \"from\": 1201, \"to\": 1213}, {\"ngram\": \"instance\", \"from\": 1230, \"to\": 1238}, {\"ngram\": \"the basis\", \"from\": 1243, \"to\": 1252}, {\"ngram\": \"self-declared gender identity\", \"from\": 1256, \"to\": 1285}, {\"ngram\": \"increasingly numerous exceptions\", \"from\": 1308, \"to\": 1340}, {\"ngram\": \"the interests\", \"from\": 1344, \"to\": 1357}, {\"ngram\": \"inclusion\", \"from\": 1361, \"to\": 1370}, {\"ngram\": \"Khelif\", \"from\": 1411, \"to\": 1417}, {\"ngram\": \"Lin\", \"from\": 1422, \"to\": 1425}, {\"ngram\": \"no legs\", \"from\": 1451, \"to\": 1458}, {\"ngram\": \"certain progressive enclaves\", \"from\": 1470, \"to\": 1498}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Second, any eligibility standard-like the IOC's framework-that denies or disregards sex-linked biology is necessarily category-defeating.\", \"from\": 1501, \"to\": 1638, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1543, \"end\": 1546, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 7.998446553957215e-16, \"text\": \"IOC\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"sex-linked biology\", \"from\": 1585, \"to\": 1603}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Finally, federations that are committed to the female category and to one-for-one equality for their female athletes must step up and do two things.\", \"from\": 1640, \"to\": 1788, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"federations\", \"from\": 1649, \"to\": 1660}, {\"ngram\": \"the female category\", \"from\": 1683, \"to\": 1702}, {\"ngram\": \"one-for-one equality\", \"from\": 1710, \"to\": 1730}, {\"ngram\": \"their female athletes\", \"from\": 1735, \"to\": 1756}, {\"ngram\": \"two things\", \"from\": 1777, \"to\": 1787}]}, {\"sentence\": \"They must craft evidence-based rules and then stick to them consistently.\", \"from\": 1789, \"to\": 1862, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"evidence-based rules\", \"from\": 1805, \"to\": 1825}]}, {\"sentence\": \"And they must seriously embrace other opportunities to welcome gender diversity within their sports.\", \"from\": 1863, \"to\": 1963, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"other opportunities\", \"from\": 1895, \"to\": 1914}, {\"ngram\": \"gender diversity\", \"from\": 1926, \"to\": 1942}, {\"ngram\": \"their sports\", \"from\": 1950, \"to\": 1962}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Start your day withReason.\", \"from\": 1965, \"to\": 1991, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"your day\", \"from\": 1971, \"to\": 1979}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Get a daily brief of the most important stories and trends every weekday morning when you subscribe toReason Roundup.\", \"from\": 1992, \"to\": 2109, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2101, \"end\": 2108, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Glyphosate\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 4.616697506225146e-25, \"text\": \"Roundup\", \"types\": [\"Q11173\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Glyphosate\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Glyphosate\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"a daily brief\", \"from\": 1996, \"to\": 2009}, {\"ngram\": \"the most important stories\", \"from\": 2013, \"to\": 2039}, {\"ngram\": \"trends\", \"from\": 2044, \"to\": 2050}]}, {\"sentence\": \"NEXT:Today in Supreme Court History: August 8, 2009 Eugene Volokhis the Thomas M. Siebel Senior Fellow at the Hoover Institution at Stanford, and the Gary T. Schwartz Distinguished Professor of Law Emeritus and Distinguished Research Professor at UCLA School of Law.\", \"from\": 2111, \"to\": 2378, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2125, \"end\": 2138, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Supreme_Court_of_the_United_States\", \"score\": 0.9999999996962288, \"rank\": 2.2766199164897381e-10, \"text\": \"Supreme Court\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://d